data.title: Is it Stephen or Steven? Are the two names interchangeable?
data.meta_description:
Answer (1 of 5): They are two alternate spellings of the same etymological name (Greek, "[victory] crown"). Choosing the wrong one is a misspelling/error. For foreign names that are transliterated into English, there is often more than one canonical way to spell it (e.g., Osama/Usama).
